Figure 1 Bird Data

bird.dat <- read.csv("Birds.DataCoallation.20200727.csv",na.strings=c("", "NA"), header=TRUE,sep=",")

#--------------------------------------------------------#
### Number of viruses 2008 VS 2020 ####
#create dataframe
(Bird.NumberOfViruses<-data.frame("Year"=c("2008", "2020_all", "2020_ICTV" ), NumberOfViruses=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y")),
                                                                                                length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2020..Y.=="Y")),
                                                                                                length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2020..Y.=="Y" & bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y" )) )) )
##        Year NumberOfViruses
## 1      2008             164
## 2  2020_all             463
## 3 2020_ICTV             232
#plot
(p1<-ggplot(Bird.NumberOfViruses, aes(Year, NumberOfViruses)) + geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="#2171b5")+ 
  geom_text(aes(label=NumberOfViruses), size=4, vjust=-0.25) + ylab("Number of Virus Species"))

#--------------------------------------------------------#
## Proportion of Viruses causing disease in 2008 vs 2020

#create dataframe
(Bird.Disease<-data.frame("Year"=c("2008", "2020_all", "2020_ICTV"), 
                     NumberOfViruses=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y")),
                                       length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2020..Y.=="Y")), 
                                       length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2020..Y.=="Y" & bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y" )) ),
                    
                     Disease.Yes=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y" & bird.dat$Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.== "Y")),
                                  length(which(bird.dat$Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.== "Y")),
                                  length(which(bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y"  & bird.dat$Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.== "Y" )) ),
                    
                     Disease.No=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y" & bird.dat$Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.== "N")),
                                 length(which(bird.dat$Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.== "N")),
                                 length(which(bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y"  & bird.dat$Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.== "N")) ) ))
##        Year NumberOfViruses Disease.Yes Disease.No
## 1      2008             164         105         59
## 2  2020_all             463         207        256
## 3 2020_ICTV             232         128        104
#calculate proportion with 95% CI
(Bird.Disease[c("PointEst", "Lower", "Upper")]<-binconf(Bird.Disease$Disease.Yes, Bird.Disease$NumberOfViruses, alpha=0.05,
            method=c("wilson"),
            include.x=FALSE, include.n=FALSE, return.df=FALSE))
##   PointEst     Lower     Upper
##  0.6402439 0.5643567 0.7097115
##  0.4470842 0.4024164 0.4926229
##  0.5517241 0.4874056 0.6143577
#plot
(p2<-ggplot(Bird.Disease, aes(Year, (PointEst*100))) + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=(Lower*100), ymax=(Upper*100), width=.5)) +geom_point(stat="identity", colour = "Steelblue", size = 5)+ 
  ylab( "Proportion Disease Causing (%)"))

#stats
#THREE PROPORTIONS
prop.test(as.matrix(Bird.Disease[, c("Disease.Yes", "Disease.No")]))
## 
##  3-sample test for equality of proportions without continuity
##  correction
## 
## data:  as.matrix(Bird.Disease[, c("Disease.Yes", "Disease.No")])
## X-squared = 20.07, df = 2, p-value = 4.385e-05
## alternative hypothesis: two.sided
## sample estimates:
##    prop 1    prop 2    prop 3 
## 0.6402439 0.4470842 0.5517241
pairwise.prop.test(as.matrix(Bird.Disease[, c("Disease.Yes", "Disease.No")])) 
## 
##  Pairwise comparisons using Pairwise comparison of proportions 
## 
## data:  as.matrix(Bird.Disease[, c("Disease.Yes", "Disease.No")]) 
## 
##   1       2    
## 2 9.5e-05 -    
## 3 0.097   0.023
## 
## P value adjustment method: holm
## GLM Stats test
tmp1 <- bird.dat %>%
  dplyr::filter(Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y") %>%
  dplyr::select(Virus.Species, Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.) 
tmp1$Year<-"2008"

tmp2 <- bird.dat %>%
  dplyr::select(Virus.Species, Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.) 
tmp2$Year<-"2020_all"

tmp3 <- bird.dat %>%
  dplyr::filter(Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y") %>%
  dplyr::select(Virus.Species, Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N.) 
tmp3$Year<-"2020_ICTV"

Bird.Disease_long<-rbind(tmp1, tmp2, tmp3)
Bird.Disease_long$Year<-as.factor(Bird.Disease_long$Year)

glm_Bird.Dis<-glm(Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N. ~ Year, data=Bird.Disease_long, family="binomial")
print(summary(glm_Bird.Dis))
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = Does.it.cause.disease.in.host..Y.N. ~ Year, family = "binomial", 
##     data = Bird.Disease_long)

print(anova(glm_Bird.Dis,test="Chisq"))

## Proportion of zoonotic in 2008 vs 2020

#create dataframe
(Bird.Zoonotic<-data.frame("Year"=c("2008", "2020_all", "2020_ICTV"), 
                     NumberOfViruses=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y")),
                                       length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2020..Y.=="Y")),
                                       length(which(bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y"  & bird.dat$Detected.2020..Y.=="Y"))),
                     Zoonotic.Yes=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y" & bird.dat$Recorded.zoonosis.event..Y.N.== "Y")),
                                    length(which(bird.dat$Recorded.zoonosis.event..Y.N.== "Y")),
                                    length(which(bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y"  & bird.dat$Recorded.zoonosis.event..Y.N.== "Y")) ),
                     Zoonotic.No=c(length(which(bird.dat$Detected.2008...Y.N.=="Y" & bird.dat$Recorded.zoonosis.event..Y.N.== "N")), 
                                   length(which(bird.dat$Recorded.zoonosis.event..Y.N.== "N")),
                                   length(which(bird.dat$Ratified.by.ICTV == "Y"  & bird.dat$Recorded.zoonosis.event..Y.N.== "N")) ) ))
##        Year NumberOfViruses Zoonotic.Yes Zoonotic.No
## 1      2008             164           43         120
## 2  2020_all             463           49         412
## 3 2020_ICTV             232           47         184
#calculate proportion with 95% CI
(Bird.Zoonotic[c("PointEst", "Lower", "Upper")]<-binconf(Bird.Zoonotic$Zoonotic.Yes, Bird.Zoonotic$NumberOfViruses, alpha=0.05,
                                                   method=c("wilson"),
                                                   include.x=FALSE, include.n=FALSE, return.df=FALSE))
##   PointEst      Lower     Upper
##  0.2621951 0.20087583 0.3343999
##  0.1058315 0.08098222 0.1371678
##  0.2025862 0.15590618 0.2589550
#plot
(p3<-ggplot(Bird.Zoonotic, aes(Year, (PointEst*100))) + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=(Lower*100), ymax=(Upper*100), width=.5)) + geom_point(stat="identity", colour = "Steelblue", size = 5)+ 
  ylab( "Proportion Zoonotic (%)"))

#stats
#Three proportions
prop.test(as.matrix(Bird.Zoonotic[, c("Zoonotic.Yes", "Zoonotic.No")]))
## 
##  3-sample test for equality of proportions without continuity
##  correction
## 
## data:  as.matrix(Bird.Zoonotic[, c("Zoonotic.Yes", "Zoonotic.No")])

##  Pairwise comparisons using Pairwise comparison of proportions 
##

##

Figure 2

#Clean up date data and merge all those viruses described before 1995 together
bird.dat$Year2<-bird.dat$Year
levels(bird.dat$Year2)[levels(bird.dat$Year2)=="<1995"] <- "1995"

fish.dat$Year2<-fish.dat$Year
levels(fish.dat$Year2)[levels(fish.dat$Year2)=="<1995"] <- "1995"

shrew.dat$Year2<-shrew.dat$Year
levels(shrew.dat$Year2)[levels(shrew.dat$Year2)=="<1995"] <- "1995"

Orthomyxo.dat$Year2<-Orthomyxo.dat$Year
levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)[levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)=="<1990"] <- "1995"
levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)[levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)=="<1990/2014"] <- "1995"
levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)[levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)=="<1990/2005"] <- "1995"
levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)[levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2)=="?/2014"] <- "1995"
Orthomyxo.dat$Year2<-as.numeric(as.character(Orthomyxo.dat$Year2))  

#make the dataframes
Bird.Year<-aggregate(Virus.Species ~ Year2, dat=bird.dat, FUN=length)
Fish.Year<-aggregate(Virus.Species ~ Year2, dat=fish.dat, FUN=length)
Orthomyxo.Year<-aggregate(Virus.Species ~ Year2, dat=Orthomyxo.dat, FUN=length)
Shrew.Year<-aggregate(Virus.Species ~ Year2 , dat=shrew.dat, FUN=length)

#change to numeric
Bird.Year$Year2<-as.numeric(as.character(Bird.Year$Year2))
Fish.Year$Year2<-as.numeric(as.character(Fish.Year$Year2))
Shrew.Year$Year2<-as.numeric(as.character(Shrew.Year$Year2))
Orthomyxo.Year$Year2<-as.numeric(as.character(Orthomyxo.Year$Year2))

#calcuate cumulative
Bird.Year[, 3] <- cumsum(Bird.Year[, 2])
Fish.Year[, 3] <- cumsum(Fish.Year[, 2])
Shrew.Year[, 3] <- cumsum(Shrew.Year[, 2])
Orthomyxo.Year[, 3] <- cumsum(Orthomyxo.Year[, 2])

#plots
coeff1<-2.67 #this is a multiplier between the first axis and the second. so max of axis 1 is 150 (here *3 gets to you to the 450 max on axis 2)
(p23<-ggplot(Bird.Year, aes(x=Year2))+
  geom_bar(aes(y=Virus.Species), fill="#2171b5", stat = "identity")+
  geom_line(aes(y=V3/coeff1))+
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "Number of Virus Species",
    sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*coeff1, name="Cumulative Number of Virus species")) +
  scale_x_continuous("Year", breaks = c(1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015, 2020)) )

coeff2<-2 
(p24<-ggplot(Fish.Year, aes(x=Year2))+
    geom_bar(aes(y=Virus.Species), fill="#6baed6", stat = "identity") +
    geom_line(aes(y=V3/coeff2))+
    scale_y_continuous(

## Using 2020 data, look at # viruses vs publications

#clean up data
levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Host2)[levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Host2)=="Birds"] <- "Bird"
levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Host2)[levels(Orthomyxo.dat$Host2)=="Humans"] <- "Human"

#check
aggregate(Number.of.papers.in.Pubmed~Host2, dat=Orthomyxo.dat, FUN=sum)
##          Host2 Number.of.papers.in.Pubmed
## 1   Amphibians                          1
## 2         Bird                         27
## 3         Fish                        305
## 4        Human                        865
## 5    Influenza                      51131
## 6 Invertebrate                         47
## 7       Mammal                        181
aggregate(Virus.Species~Host2, dat=Orthomyxo.dat, FUN=length)
##          Host2 Virus.Species
## 1   Amphibians             1
## 2         Bird             9
## 3         Fish            11
## 4        Human             5
## 5    Influenza             2
## 6 Invertebrate            41
## 7       Mammal             4
#make dataframe
test<-data.frame(aggregate(Number.of.papers.in.Pubmed~Host2, dat=Orthomyxo.dat, FUN=sum),
                 (aggregate(Virus.Species~Host2, dat=Orthomyxo.dat, FUN=length)) ) 
test$Host2.1<-NULL               
test$TotalPapers<-sum(test$Number.of.papers.in.Pubmed)
test$Proportion<-(test$Number.of.papers.in.Pubmed/test$TotalPapers)*100

#reorder
test$Host2 <- factor(test$Host2,levels = c("Influenza", "Human", "Mammal","Bird", "Fish", "Amphibians", "Invertebrate"))

#correlation
summary(lm(Proportion ~  Virus.Species, data=test))$r.squared 
## [1] 0.07305931
#correlation plot
ggplot(test, aes(Proportion, Virus.Species, color=Host2))+geom_point(size = 5) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette="Paired")+
  annotate("text",x = 50, y=30,label=c("R^2=0.07305931"))+
  annotate("text",x = 80, y=7,label=c("2 species, 97% publications"))+
  annotate("text",x = 20, y=38,label=c("57% species, 17 publications"))+ 
  xlab( "Proportion of Orthomyxovirus papers in PubMed (%), n=52557") + ylab( "Number of Virus Species Described")

ggsave("Pub.Corr.pdf", width=9, height=6)
